The paper deals with the construction of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The codes are designed to correct errors in communication channels, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of matrices, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and network information theory (cs.NI).
